- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method for semi-supervised learning on graph-based datasets using graph convolutional networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves an architecture change mimicking techniques from Model Order Reduction, which is a common approach in AI research. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Graph convolutional networks have been successfully applied in computer vision tasks, and the paper discusses the use of low-rank filters for improved accuracy and runtime acceleration. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on semi-supervised learning on graph-based datasets, which is a common problem in social and information networks research. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed method involves the use of neural networks (graph convolutional networks) for semi-supervised learning, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
